ong with Waves and Salvo, are part of the settlement of Chicamacomico. Rodanthe includes the original Chicamacomico Life-Saving Station, decommissioned in 1954, but now a museum. Rodanthe is served by North Carolina Highway 12 which runs north/south ","credit":"Ken Lund from Reno, Nevada, USA · CC BY-SA 2.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Approaching_Rodanthe,_Outer_Banks,_North_Carolina,_Highway_12_(14267908689).jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d6/Approaching_Rodanthe%2C_Outer_Banks%2C_North_Carolina%2C_Highway_12_%2814451196681%29.jpg/1280px-Approaching_Rodanthe%2C_Outer_Banks%2C_North_Carolina%2C_Highway_12_%2814451196681%29.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d6/Approaching_Rodanthe%2C_Outer_Banks%2C_North_Carolina%2C_Highway_12_%2814451196681%29.jpg","cap":"Approaching Rodanthe, Outer Banks, North Carolina, Highway 12 (1445119","desc":"Rodanthe is an unincorporated community located in Dare County, North Carolina, on Hatteras Island, part of North Carolina's Outer Banks. Rodanthe, along with Waves and Salvo, are part of the settlement of Chicamacomico. Rodanthe includes the original Chicamacomico Life-Saving Station, decommissioned in 1954, but now a museum. Rodanthe is served by North Carolina Highway 12 which runs north/south ","credit":"Ken Lund from Reno, Nevada, USA · CC BY-SA 2.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Approaching_Rodanthe,_Outer_Banks,_North_Carolina,_Highway_12_(14451196681).jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4a/6_Miles_to_Buxton%2C_Avon%2C_North_Carolina%2C_Outer_Banks_%2814474759443%29.jpg/1280px-6_Miles_to_Buxton%2C_Avon%2C_North_Carolina%2C_Outer_Banks_%2814474759443%29.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/4a/6_Miles_to_Buxton%2C_Avon%2C_North_Carolina%2C_Outer_Banks_%2814474759443%29.jpg","cap":"6 Miles to Buxton, Avon, North Carolina, Outer Banks (14474759443)","desc":"Avon is a census-designated place(CDP) in Dare County in the State of North Carolina in the United States of America. The village is south of Salvo and north of Buxton on Hatteras Island. Historically named Kinnakeet, the village was renamed Avon by the U.S. Postal Service when a post office was established there in 1883. The U.S. Life-Saving Service constructed the Little Kinnakeet Life Saving St","credit":"Ken Lund from Reno, Nevada, USA · CC BY-SA 2.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:6_Miles_to_Buxton,_Avon,_North_Carolina,_Outer_Banks_(14474759443).jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/5_Miles_to_Duck%2C_North_Carolina_Highway_12%2C_Southern_Shores%2C_North_Carolina_%2814282500750%29.jpg/1280px-5_Miles_to_Duck%2C_North_Carolina_Highway_12%2C_Southern_Shores%2C_North_Carolina_%2814282500750%29.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/37/5_Miles_to_Duck%2C_North_Carolina_Highway_12%2C_Southern_Shores%2C_North_Carolina_%2814282500750%29.jpg","cap":"5 Miles to Duck, , Southern Shores, North Carolina (14282500750)","desc":"North Carolina Highway 12 (NC 12) is a state highway that traverses the northeastern coastline of North Carolina, linking the peninsulas and islands of the northern Outer Banks. Most sections of NC 12 are two lanes wide, and there are also two ferry routes which maintain continuity of the route as it traverses the Outer Banks region. NC 12 is part of the Outer Banks Scenic Byway one of the Nationa","credit":"Ken Lund from Reno, Nevada, USA · CC BY-SA 2.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:5_Miles_to_Duck,_North_Carolina_Highway_12,_Southern_Shores,_North_Carolina_(14282500750).jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/5_Miles_to_Duck%2C_North_Carolina_Highway_12%2C_Southern_Shores%2C_North_Carolina_%2814282500750%29_%28cropped%29.jpg/1280px-5_Miles_to_Duck%2C_North_Carolina_Highway_12%2C_Southern_Shores%2C_North_Carolina_%2814282500750%29_%